es up to $z\\sim 1,$\nwhich is well-matched by the evolution calculated archeologically from the\nabundance distributions of mono-age stellar populations at $z\\sim 0$. Overall,\nSupernova feedback could explain the trends but an impact of migration can not\nbe totally discarded. Galaxy-galaxy interactions or small satellite accretions\ncan also contribute to modify the metallicity profiles in the outer parts.\n[abridged]\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 12 Jun 2017 17:21:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-06-13"}
