 the return current is most likely primarily carried by runaway\nelectrons from the tail of the thermal distribution rather than the bulk\ndrifting thermal electrons. For these cases, anomalous resistivity is not\nrequired.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 13 Jun 2017 03:13:54 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 4 Jan 2018 15:57:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-01-08"}
